{%- comment -%}
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SENTRY ERROR MONITORING (installed 2026-05-07)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Loader Script — fetches the full Sentry SDK lazily. Project key is embedded in the URL (it is public, not
a secret — Sentry's loader keys are designed to be exposed client-side, like Google Analytics IDs).

Loaded BEFORE bb-defensive-shim and BEFORE Google Tag Manager so Sentry's window error handler is registered
as early as possible. The defensive shim runs in capture phase with stopImmediatePropagation, so the specific
addEventListener-on-null errors we already know about will NOT reach Sentry (intentional — those are already
mitigated and we do not want to spam Sentry quota with them). Everything else bubbles up to Sentry normally.

Project: Bounty Basket Co. (the-bounty-basket.sentry.io)
Default config (per onboarding): tracesSampleRate 1.0, replaysSessionSampleRate 0.1, replaysOnErrorSampleRate 1.0
Configure further in Sentry's Project Settings UI rather than here — keeps this loader version-agnostic.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
{%- endcomment -%}
<script
  src="https://js.sentry-cdn.com/REPLACE_WITH_BOUNTY_SENTRY_KEY.min.js"
  crossorigin="anonymous"
></script>

{%- comment -%}
BB Cart Hardening 2026-05-04: Defensive shim must load FIRST (after Sentry) so it intercepts errors
from all subsequently-loaded scripts (GTM, theme, third-party apps).
{%- endcomment -%}
